    "recap_headline": "Lehigh University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "BETHLEHEM, Pa.\u00a0\u2013 Lehigh baseball play game two of its weekend series against the Navy Midshipmen at J. David Walker Field on Saturday afternoon. After earning a 3-1 win in game one, the Mountain Hawks fell 3-0 to even the series 1-1.\nNavy (13-5, 1-1 PL) starter Matt Archibald earned the win after going 8.0 complete innings with nine strikeouts, five hits, and three walks while Tyler Grenn picked up the save. Lehigh (4-11, 1-1 PL) starter\nCole Leaman\nwas credited with the loss after allowing two earned runs with three strikeouts in 3.2 innings pitched.\nArchibald and Leaman traded scoreless innings through the first and second frames. The Mids brought home a run in the top of the third on an RBI from Andrew Manning to take a 1-0 lead. A Tyler Cripe RBI in the top of the fourth inning extended Navy's lead to two through four innings.\nMax Treonze\nentered the game for Lehigh in the fourth inning and performed admirably, keeping the Mids off the board in the fifth, sixth, seventh, and eighth innings. Navy added a run of insurance in the top of the ninth on an RBI from Joh Loudon before\nJake Mulvehill\nrecorded the final out to send the game to the bottom of the ninth. The Mountain Hawks got two baserunners aboard, but Grenn recorded the outs necessary to secure his save and the Navy victory.\nRobbie Carvelli\nwent 2-4 with a double while\nAidan Quinn\n,\nRyan Cochran\n,\nOwen Walewander\n,\nTrystan Crawford\n, and\nJack Frankovic\nalso secured hits for Lehigh.\nThe Mountain Hawks will conclude the weekend series with the Midshipmen on Sunday, March 15 at 12 p.m. at J. David Walker Field.\nLike Lehigh Baseball on\nFacebook\n, follow on\nX\n(formerly Twitter)\u00a0and\nInstagram\nfor exclusive content, team updates and more."
